{
  "number": 1806,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1806",
  "title": "API proposal: transformProvidedProps as a way to modify widgets providedProps. ",
  "body": "Because we removed the sortBy option on several widgets, a user can't modify the sorting strategy if using our widgets. However we noticed that the sorting strategy was heavily depending on the use case and the amount of data, thus, a user should be able to modify it.\r\n\r\nBecause we don't want to provide an option that has a lack of flexibility and because other use cases might come up we should add an API entry that is being able to modify the props sent to a widget.\r\n\r\n@vvo proposed to have a prop called `transformProvidedProps`. It will take the `providedProps` as a parameter, and expect to return the same `providedProps` structure.\r\nThis props, if exists, will be called each time a connector called its `getProvidedProps` function.\r\n\r\nex of usage:\r\n\r\n```js\r\n<RefinementList attributeName=\"category\" \t\r\n\t\t\t\ttransformProvidedProps={props => {\r\n      \t\t\t\tconst items = orderBy(props.items, ['label'], ['asc']);\r\n      \t\t\t\treturn {...props, items};\r\n\t\t\t\t}}\r\n/>\r\n```",
